Reasoning: The paper discusses variations of the McEliece cryptosystem, which is a public-key encryption scheme. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of spatially coupled moderate-density parity-check codes suggests a possible connection to coding theory (cs.CC). The discussion of security with respect to known attacks suggests a possible connection to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SE).
